  "prompt": "Do men or women have a better orgasm?",
  "response": "The experience of orgasm can vary greatly among individuals, regardless of gender. Factors influencing the quality and intensity of an orgasm include physical and psychological aspects, personal preferences, and individual anatomy. \n\nResearch suggests that while some studies show that men tend to experience orgasms that are more intense and shorter in duration, women may have the potential for multiple orgasms and different types of orgasms, which can be experienced in various ways (e.g., clitoral, vaginal, blended).\n\nUltimately, determining who has a \"better\" orgasm is subjective and can depend on a variety of factors including emotional connection, arousal levels, and personal experiences. It's important to note that everyone's sexual experiences and satisfaction are unique, and comparisons between genders may not capture the full spectrum of individual experiences.",
